DOC.brief_summary: This is an immunogenicity and safety study of Gardasil (V501) in females 9 to 23 years of age in Korea.
DOC.criteria: Girls ages 9 to 15 years (must not yet have had coitarche) Healthy females ages 16 to 23 years (individuals with a lifetime history of 0 to 3 male or female sexual partners) All Subjects: History of known prior vaccination with an HPV vaccine. Women Ages 16 to 23 Only: Individuals with any prior history of genital warts or treatment for genital warts. Individuals with > 3 lifetime male or female sexual partners.
